SDRplay comparison of 4 popular magnetic loop antennas

SDRplay Software Defined Radio Receiver
SDRplay Software Defined Radio Receiver

33.584 Aufrufe • 25.08.2021
In this video Mike Harwood compares 4 different active mag loop antenna at various frequencies up to 52MHz using two SDRplay RSPduos which allowed simultaneous spectrum snapshots of the 4 loops in action with real signals. These are loops from Bonito, Cross Country Wireless, LZ1AQ and Wellbrook.  …...mehr

@dazedandconfused698

vor 1 Jahr
A big thank you for all the work producing this, but I'm afraid it demonstrates very little for the following reasons and probably why not much difference between antennas has been found - 1. Why do the test during the day, when there are virtually no signals to hear- this has given very little basis for comparison. Surely what most people want to know is which antenna picks up those weak and distant signals the best and needs to be done at night. 2. Comparing visible spectrum displays is not an entirely reliable method of comparison of what can be heard, especially when looking at weak signals. I frequently find readable signals with no obvious sign of them in the spectrum e.g. NDBs Surely what we hear counts more than what we see on the spectrum.
